title: Print, "Grilles des angles d'entrée de la Place Royale de Nancy [Ironwork of the Entrance Corners of the Place Royal of Nancy] in Recueil des Ouvrages en Serrurerie.", 1698–1771
medium: Engraving on heavy cream laid paper
signed: Signed in plate, under image lower margin: inventé et executé par Lamour Serurier du Roy et gravé a Nancy part Collin Graveur du Roy
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: View of part of ironwork gate with arched grill and coat of arms of Stanislas Leszcynski on top and one ornamental vase at left.  A lantern hangs off the end of the gate supported by a decorative rocaille arm.
